Marketing Brief -- Reliance Group Holdings Inc.:
   Telemundo Unit Says Sales
   Of Syndicated Shows Grew
"Buying `Estrenos y Estrellas' {a show about the
entertainment business} versus `Entertainment Tonight' offers
Latin American broadcasters the same quality and lower price
with more relevance to their audience," said Augusto Failde,
head of international sales for Telemundo.
   In the U.S., Telemundo reaches 84% of Hispanic households
in 44 markets. About 60% of its programming is U.S.-produced,
Telemundo said. Telemundo declined to provide specific
overseas sales figures.